description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ward 3 at Royal Preston Hospital is a 19-bed unit surgical ward and an element of the Head and Neck Oncology Directorate. This is an exciting opportunity to join the regional centre covering the North West specialising in Ear, Nose and Throat and Maxillofacial illnesses and diseases, of which many patients have complex needs. Ward 3 also houses the Day of Surgery Admissions Area where you will be expected to work across both areas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full training will be given in tracheostomy, laryngectomy care, airway management and the psychological effects that can occur with regards to altered body image. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to appoint band 5 nurses both newly qualified and experienced to work across our ward and surgical admissions unit. You will join a friendly and supportive team of nurses and will be working alongside highly skilled doctors, clinical nurse specialists and an array of allied health care professionals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview Date: To be confirmed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
